name: "Pig - capacity"
description: The first digitized exhibition of the master of pottery, Ivan Ivanovich Loboichenko. Ivan Ivanovich Loboychenko created this work 25 years ago at the Keramik art plant. At that time, the traditional works of the figures of various animals: bulls, horses, pigs, deer, and these were containers for liquid. Nobody made pigs, only he. Options: Height - 330 mm Width - 320 mm Length - 480 mm Material - clay, manufacturing process - potter's wheel, modeling, glaze, engraving.
